1-f354-4e5c-acb5-eee73741984d.png","tw":"\"labourmatt\""},{"n":"Bridget Caroline Hilton","p":"Green Party","v":256,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132238"},{"n":"Eric Perry","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":220,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112441"},{"n":"Abdul Qadus","p":"Independent","v":183,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"82187","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/132239/06efedcc-d7f4-4d17-bd5e-97e96870d2a6.png"}]},{"ward":"Gornal","seats":1,"turnout_pct":42.42,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Chris Whitehouse","p":"Reform UK","v":2532,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"132252"},{"n":"Claire Sullivan","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":854,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"87812"},{"n":"Jeff Ndlovu","p":"Labour Party","v":382,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112491"},{"n":"Kaz Evans","p":"Green Party","v":300,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"132251"},{"n":"Stephen Holmes","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":140,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111965"}]},{"ward":"Halesowen North","seats":1,"turnout_pct":40.42,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Stuart Carl Henley","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1347,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"35150","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/35150.png","stmt":"I fought to become a Councillor over many years. I did this to help locals and the area, not because of politics. UKIP were active throughout the Dudley Borough helping out with many projects, so I joined them in approx. 2004 and became active with some of their projects and many of my own. It took me 10 years to get elected, but the time did not stop me working to help so many. Prior my councillor term ending, a few of us discussed a local party and the idea grew and now we have the start of a local, community party.\n\nNow the work starts for the community party and I will do all I can to make this work.\n\nAlso along side the above I've been a fire fighter for West Midlands Fire Service since 1998, prior to that I was in the Auxiliary Royal Air Force at Brize Norton.","tw":"\"HenleyStatic\""},{"n":"Fiona Murray","p":"Labour Party","v":1182,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111960"},{"n":"Aveena Sherwani","p":"Reform UK","v":792,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"132264"},{"n":"Ash Flavin","p":"Green Party","v":482,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"low","pid":"99640"},{"n":"Tracey Gregg","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":114,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"82191"}]},{"ward":"Halesowen South","seats":1,"turnout_pct":47.36,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Andrew Barnfield","p":"Reform UK","v":1684,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132271"},{"n":"Thomas Geoffrey Russon","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1287,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"87805"},{"n":"Michael Hanley","p":"Labour Party","v":770,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111987"},{"n":"James Robert Windridge","p":"Green Party","v":526,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"71465","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/71465/094f15da-622f-4e08-b195-2c179edceb70.png","stmt":"I’m standing as your Green Party candidate in Halesowen South because I believe our community deserves better—cleaner streets, safer neighbourhoods, and a future we can be proud to pass on to our children.\n\nToo many people here feel overlooked. From potholes and neglected green spaces to rising living costs and pressure on local services, it’s clear that Halesowen South needs a stronger voice. I want to be that voice—standing up for residents, not party politics.\n\nI’m committed to protecting and improving our local environment. That means tackling fly-tipping, improving air quality, and safeguarding the green spaces we all value. But it also means practical action—better insulation for homes to cut energy bills, and supporting local transport options that actually work for people.\n\nI also want to strengthen our sense of community. Supporting local businesses, investing in youth opportunities, and making sure everyone feels safe and included are not “nice to have”—they’re essential.\n\nThe Green Party stands for fairness, honesty, and long-term thinking. I’m not here to make empty promises—I’m here to listen, to act, and to work hard for Halesowen South every day.\nIf you want a councillor who will put people, community, and the environment first, I’d be proud to have your support.\n\nAs your Green Party candidate; I'll always put People and Planet at the center of what I do."},{"n":"Caroline Benton","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":199,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"99629"}]},{"ward":"Hayley Green & Cradley South","seats":1,"turnout_pct":43.46,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Jon Mucklow","p":"Reform UK","v":1573,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132298"},{"n":"Bex Collins","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1255,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"111985"},{"n":"Julian Hammond-Miller","p":"Labour Party","v":609,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132296"},{"n":"Zach Beed","p":"Green Party","v":381,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"132295"},{"n":"Alison Joanne Hunt","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":173,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"132297"}]},{"ward":"Kingswinford North & Wall Heath","seats":1,"turnout_pct":50.39,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Mark Webb","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1983,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"59199","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/59199/575846ba-24be-473f-a0af-a9ab014ffdb3.png"},{"n":"Stephen Richard Cole","p":"Reform UK","v":1913,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132299"},{"n":"Jacqueline Ann Foster","p":"Labour Party","v":456,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132300"},{"n":"Ninette Harris","p":"Green Party","v":318,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"132301"},{"n":"Charlie Passmore","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":150,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"132302"}]},{"ward":"Kingswinford South","seats":1,"turnout_pct":44.81,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Graham Howes","p":"Reform UK","v":1888,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132304"},{"n":"Luke Johnson","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1415,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"16229","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/16229/a556d775-e572-4d98-b2f1-de24df70dd40.png"},{"n":"Simon Geoffrey Daniel","p":"Labour Party","v":525,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"94663","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/94663/c33499d0-aa4d-4918-b90b-a587b20b930e.png"},{"n":"Dom Palermo","p":"Green Party","v":430,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"132305"},{"n":"Simon Paul Hanson","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":173,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"16257"}]},{"ward":"Lye & Stourbridge North","seats":1,"turnout_pct":36.57,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Lisa Marie Clinton","p":"Reform UK","v":1348,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132329"},{"n":"Ellen Hope Cobb","p":"Labour Party","v":695,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"59010","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/59010.png","tw":"\"TheEllenHope\""},{"n":"Naz Ahmed","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":477,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"45241"},{"n":"Julia Annette Savage","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":448,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132331"},{"n":"Danny Hussain","p":"Green Party","v":342,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132330"},{"n":"Matt Cook","p":"The Black Country Party","v":163,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"87802","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/87802/e0229b8f-3b3a-4407-8e76-7456768dd86e.png"}]},{"ward":"Netherton & Holly Hall","seats":1,"turnout_pct":31.95,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Jack Thompson","p":"Reform UK","v":1622,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"126706","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/126706/30def674-18ed-45cc-91b8-77de369139f9.png","stmt":"Netherton and Holly Hall has some brilliant people, but the area isn’t getting the attention it deserves.\nMy opponents live here, and that’s fine, we all see the same issues every day.\nThe difference is how we fix them, not where we sleep.\nIf I’m elected, here’s what I’ll do:\n\n✔ Cleaner, safer streets\nHow:\nWork with residents to map fly-tipping hotspots\nPush for targeted enforcement and named officers responsible\nPress the council to use CCTV and fines properly, not as a PR line\n\n✔ A council that listens\nHow:\nHold regular monthly surgeries in the ward\nGive residents straight answers — no runaround\nPublish what I’m doing so people can see progress\n\n✔ Fairness for families and small businesses\nHow:\nChase repairs and landlord issues until they’re done, not ignored\nBack local traders and markets instead of pointless vanity projects\nPush back on endless charges being dumped on hard-working residents\n\nI’m not in this for position or party titles.\nI’m standing because this ward deserves someone who’ll graft for it every day, not just turn up for elections.\nNetherton and Holly Hall deserve better and I’ll roll my sleeves up to deliver it.","tw":"\"JackThompsonwlc\"","bd":"1999"},{"n":"Shaneila Karamat Mughal","p":"Labour Party","v":691,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"59198","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/59198/df3d94f8-5076-4840-9773-adc24d7ee3e3.png","tw":"\"shaneilamughal\""},{"n":"Manjit Kaur","p":"Green Party","v":423,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"132334"},{"n":"James Warner Tye","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":375,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112468"},{"n":"Richard Lloyd Priest","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":150,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"79778"}]},{"ward":"Norton","seats":1,"turnout_pct":51.97,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Phil Boaler","p":"Reform UK","v":1691,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132335","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/132335/cc1be3f5-fbf6-4195-9978-55bcbe4cc163.png"},{"n":"Alan Harry Hopwood","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1350,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"16336","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/16336/8889afe0-d277-4f8f-a539-97c12528bbcf.png"},{"n":"Stephen James Price","p":"Green Party","v":1030,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"99644","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/99644/4ed46d68-55e5-49d6-859c-1bcfe0d28685.png","stmt":"Dear Residents,\n\nNational polling is consistent: **the majority of people want change**—and I think that reflects what many in our community are feeling too.\nI’m Stephen Price, a local parent, a leader in the education sector, and your candidate in the upcoming election. My children have been educated here in Norton, I work mostly from my home in Oldswinford, and I’ve been a school governor at Redhill.\nI am standing to be your councillor for Norton because I care about community. **I am committed to being a strong and effective representative**—someone who listens, brings fresh ideas, and works hard to deliver meaningful change.\n\n- **An inclusive, transparent and collaborative approach**: I bring an open, inclusive, and collaborative approach to work. In my early career, as a scientist working on wildlife health, I worked with researchers from 16 countries and published reports with more than 100 other people. As a civil servant, after the pandemic, I was the technical lead for a major government data sharing project (between Ofqual, the DfE and UCAS). **I believe in working together to get things done and being open about how decisions are made. The Green Party doesn’t tell me how to vote.**\n- **Leadership and transformation**: I have led teams for public and private organisations, building capability, engagement and shared ways of working. **I am good at finding new ways to do things that help organisations overcome challenges** because I lead on the design, delivery and communication of new solutions.\n- **Making sure local people have their say and are proud of this area**: I am a board member of Stourbridge Community Land Trust, supporting the development of sustainable, comfortable, and affordable homes for local people. **I think our area is best served by working together as a community**, whether that be on housing, energy or transport.\n\nYou will be voting for one councillor representing Norton on Dudley council. **I can win here and will work hard to do the","bd":"1980"},{"n":"Matt Broad","p":"Labour Party","v":492,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112469"},{"n":"Lee Robert Furness","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":215,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"132336"}]},{"ward":"Pedmore & Stourbridge East","seats":1,"turnout_pct":49.04,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Jason Douglas Thorne","p":"Reform UK","v":1482,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132347"},{"n":"Dave Borley","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1370,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"82186"},{"n":"Nigel Paul Kirkham","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":638,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112475"},{"n":"Mark Christopher Kent","p":"Labour Party","v":560,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112474"},{"n":"Beth Scrimshaw","p":"Green Party","v":496,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112477"}]},{"ward":"Quarry Bank & Dudley Wood","seats":1,"turnout_pct":33.89,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Rob Clinton","p":"Reform UK","v":1891,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132355"},{"n":"Jules Singh","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":489,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"132357"},{"n":"Simon Mark Ballinger","p":"Green Party","v":400,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132354"},{"n":"Errol Law