,"m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112499"},{"n":"Katherine Alice Poole","p":"Green Party","v":355,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132370"},{"n":"Mollie Jo Priest","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":130,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"82157"},{"n":"David Reynolds","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":30,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112502"}]},{"ward":"St. Thomas's","seats":1,"turnout_pct":35.76,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Adeela Qayyum","p":"Labour Party","v":1415,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"99619"},{"n":"Chris Chivers","p":"Reform UK","v":1224,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"132372"},{"n":"Zia Ur Rehman Qari","p":"Green Party","v":399,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"99618","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/99618/57466339-5882-488c-a7cd-32b3e15dd159.png","bd":"1976"},{"n":"Shakeela Bibi","p":"Independent","v":358,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"112498","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/112498/3136d2ee-7dd2-4700-98f9-123f810e32cf.png"},{"n":"Muhammad Najeeb","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":295,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"99617"},{"n":"Rob Johns","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":120,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"99647"}]},{"ward":"Upper Gornal & Woodsetton","seats":1,"turnout_pct":39.91,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Marco Longhi","p":"Reform UK","v":2533,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"52116","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/52116.png","tw":"\"marcolonghi4dn\"","url":"\"https://www.marcolonghi.org.uk/\"","bd":"1967"},{"n":"Mushtaq Hussain","p":"Labour Party","v":506,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"39586"},{"n":"Zoe Bradley","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":429,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132401"},{"n":"Charlie Hilken","p":"Green Party","v":320,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"132402"},{"n":"Elaine Catherine Sheppard","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":115,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"39183","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/39183.png"}]},{"ward":"Wollaston & Stourbridge Town","seats":2,"turnout_pct":49.04,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Kam MacLeod","p":"Reform UK","v":1464,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132414"},{"n":"Andrew Southall","p":"Reform UK","v":1324,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"115540","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/116524/9180ae76-09e0-4950-a829-bd4c5b56bc72.png","stmt":"My name is Andrew Southall and I am standing for Reform UK in the upcoming General Election for Dudley, formally Dudley North but now incorporating the ward of Pensnett and Brockmoor. Much like you, I want my country back. I want to prise it out of the hands of the woke, globalist establishment and give it back to the citizens of this country. I also want to be a first class representative of Dudley, the town I grew up in. I want to represent you with a loud common sense voice in parliament, and run my constituency office like a business.\n\nA business that puts its customers, the taxpayer and those in genuine need, first. Right now, nobody is getting good service, the mood is rightly demuir if not downright angry. If you elect me, my constituency office will be comprised of local folk who know the area, understand the issues and will deal with the ailments of the day to the best of our ability.\n\nI will be passionate about my job in my constituency office when not causing a fuss in Westminster, and will be at my consituency surgeries in person for you to come and hold me to account. I am in this to fix my town and country, and will respect the public dime as something to be treated sacred. In order to get there to do this for you, I need you to tell your friends and family about Reform UK and vote for me.\n\nI was brought up in Gornal, and went to Dudley college after leaving Ellowes Hall secondary school. I left school right on the cusp of the recession and gained many strings to my bow in what was a very uncertain world. My work experience includes accountancy, barbering, working on priceless supercars, and I am also a qualified telecoms technician.\n\nI have turned my hand to many things in life, and now I turn my hand to give the lying, failing political establishment a well deserved spanking. They deserve it for truly letting us all down. Right now on top of my political campaign I am working towards my AAT book-keeping certificates, as due to the recession I was not","tw":"\"ReformUKDudley\""},{"n":"Lois Bramall","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1202,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"39180"},{"n":"David John Sheppard","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1083,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"39184"},{"n":"Richard Andrew Prosser","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":894,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132415"},{"n":"Jason Robert Griffin","p":"Labour Party","v":856,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"87811","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/87811/3abec56d-d86d-448d-bc43-9895636290f5.png"},{"n":"Steve Hancock","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":856,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"124331","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/124331/18b421d3-f544-46fe-a621-44ecfdc3ec6a.png"},{"n":"Marie Elizabeth Fields","p":"Labour Party","v":814,"r":8,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132412"},{"n":"Linda Carol Foster","p":"Green Party","v":636,"r":9,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112504"},{"n":"Ruth Jayne Battersea","p":"Green Party","v":576,"r":10,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"132411"},{"n":"Ken Moore","p":"Freedom Alliance","v":61,"r":11,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"87816","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/87816/3285b12e-0e9b-45de-9caa-24e90e3701e6.png","stmt":"A retired teacher, now maintaining my hobby as an amateur musician and my philosophical interests, I came with my family to live in Stourbridge in 1989 and this area has become my home - so I very much want the best for Wollaston and Stourbridge Town.\n Freedom Alliance is a Libertarian political party born out of the freedom movement as a direct response to government overreach into every aspect of our lives, especially since 2020. For those people here who are, for whatever reason, now feeling disappointed in local political parties, I have chosen to stand as candidate with Freedom Alliance to provide an alternative place for your vote.\n\nWe would probably all prefer to see the efficient running of local communities put before big party politics. Instead I perceive a pervading, growing Globalist NGO influence in the performance of the big parties which filters down to all local councils. It colours the stage and backdrop of their working, setting parameters for local politicians who toe their party line.\n\nFreedom Alliance includes people from all political backgrounds, focusing on what is right for the people, not what is right for corporate interests that seem to have captured and now steer the big parties. I stand because I have great concerns about the continual erosion of our freedoms.\n\nYou may have also become aware that farming is under threat due to policies that are taking farm land out of production with the consequent insecurity to our food supplies. I see that the policies of globalist, non government organisations have created a political agenda that descends on us like “Clouds of mystery pourin’ confusion on the ground.” (From ‘Who’ll Stop The Rain,’ by Creedence Clearwater Revival)\n\nI endorse local grass roots initiatives to spring up in freedom as positive possibilities for change in the community, from the option of home education to Community Supported Agriculture. There are independent community organic farming enterprises happening in many places,","bd":"1952"}]},{"ward":"Wordsley North","seats":1,"turnout_pct":41.86,"results_url":"https://online.dudley.gov.uk/elections/local2026-live.asp","candidates":[{"n":"Samuel James Hussey","p":"Reform UK","v":1788,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128769","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128769/6599227d-9a7a-4440-b93c-675eb9497321.png"},{"n":"Matt Rogers","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1056,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"59220"},{"n":"Keith Archer","p":"Labour Party","v":554,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"87817","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/87817/e8dae705-5429-4105-9b0e-aa422fbe2440.png"},{"n":"Alex Hughes","p":"Green Party","v":320,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"132436"},{"n":"Dave Woolley","p":"The Black Country Party","v":208,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112362"},{"n":"Christopher Ashley Bramall","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":153,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"2601","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/552695ad59bbc5c063445be7.png","tw":"\"ChrisBramall\